SS Sergeant Oskar Groening is being tried on 300,000 counts of accessory to murder . 
  He is accused of complicity in the deaths of 425,000 Jews between May and July 1944 at the Nazi death camp in Poland . 
  He told the court on Wednesday how he was put on a 24-hour shift guarding the ramp where Jews were brought to the gas chambers . 
  He said he was on duty when 450,000 Hungarian Jews arrived at the camp and were gassed to death . 
  Groening said he is 'morally guilty' but not directly responsible for the deaths . 
 